{"module_name":"clone-string-inside-memory-arena","package_name":"clone-string-inside-memory-arena","build_type":"library","description":"Foundation L1 freestanding strdup: measure a NUL-terminated string, reserve length+1 bytes from the bump arena, copy the bytes (terminator included), and return the owned duplicate. Variant-A-pure native schema: the length+1 size is computed into a temp local before the allocate call (no compound-expression call argument). Composes the three lower foundation primitives (strlen scan, mmap arena allocator, counted byte copy) — the first multi-package composition of the glibc-free libc. Replaces the compiler's strdup call sites on the native target.","function_definitions":{"clone-string-inside-memory-arena":{"return_type":"str","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"s","parameter_type":"str"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"determine-string-character-sequence-length","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"s"}],"result_assignment_variable":"string_length","result_type":"i64"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"size_with_terminator","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"alu_operation","operator":"+","target":"size_with_terminator","lhs":{"value":"string_length"},"rhs":{"value":"one"}},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"allocate-character-buffer-inside-memory-arena","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"size_with_terminator"}],"result_assignment_variable":"duplicate_buffer","result_type":"str"},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"transfer-memory-bytes-between-buffers","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"duplicate_buffer"},{"kind":"var","value":"s"},{"kind":"var","value":"size_with_